threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, no section header

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is an ARM-based DDoS bot, likely a Mirai variant. It connects to a hardcoded C2 server at 41.216.189.185 (seen in function `sub_1231c`). The binary contains multiple DDoS attack functions, including HTTP floods with randomized User-Agent strings (e.g., in `sub_9e54`), SSDP amplification floods (M-SEARCH string in `sub_1102c`), and generic UDP/TCP floods using custom payloads (e.g., `/x38/xFJ/...` in `sub_c12c`). It also features a process-killer module (`sub_1172c`) to terminate competing malware by scanning the `/proc` directory. Malicious intent is further confirmed by the presence of taunting strings like "Self Rep Fucking NeTiS...".
